== Career == In the 2nd year of Emperor Tenji’s reign (663), Osamu led troops as a middle general during the campaign against {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅}}, serving under the senior general {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Wani no Wakako|ja|上毛野稚子}} and rear general {{ill|Abe no Hirafu|ja|阿倍比羅夫}}. He reportedly commanded an army of 27,000 soldiers.<ref>''Nihon Shoki,'' Emperor Tenji, 2nd Year, 3rd Month entry.</ref> His involvement in the {{ill|Battle of Baekgang|ja|白村江の戦い}} is mentioned,<ref>''Nihon Shoki,'' Emperor Tenji, 2nd Year, 8th Month, 27th and 28th Day entries.</ref> but whether he survived and returned to Japan remains unclear.<ref>''Nihon Shoki,'' Emperor Tenji, 2nd Year, 9th Month entries (7th, 11th, 13th, 24th, and 25th Days).</ref>
